{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "rsv:second-chronicles.11",
    "translationId": "rsv",
    "bookSlug": "second-chronicles",
    "chapterNumber": 11,
    "referenceLabel": "2 Chronicles 11",
    "summary": "Source text for 2 Chronicles 11 in Revised Standard Version."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "rsv:second-chronicles.11.1",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "second-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Chronicles 11:1",
      "text": "When Rehoboam came to Jerusalem, he assembled the house of Judah, and Benjamin, a hundred and eighty thousand chosen warriors, to fight against Israel, to restore the kingdom to Rehoboam.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:second-chronicles.11.2",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "second-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Chronicles 11:2",
      "text": "But the word of the Lord came to Shemaiah the man of God:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:second-chronicles.11.3",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "second-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Chronicles 11:3",
      "text": "“Say to Rehoboam the son of Solomon king of Judah, and to all Israel in Judah and Benjamin,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:second-chronicles.11.4",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "second-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Chronicles 11:4",
      "text": "‘Thus says the Lord, You shall not go up or fight against your brethren. Return every man to his home, for this thing is from me.’ ” So they hearkened to the word of the Lord, and returned and did not go against Jeroboam.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:second-chronicles.11.5",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "second-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Chronicles 11:5",
      "text": "Rehoboam dwelt in Jerusalem, and he built cities for defense in Judah.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:second-chronicles.11.6",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "second-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Chronicles 11:6",
      "text": "He built Bethlehem, Etam, Tekoa,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:second-chronicles.11.7",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "second-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Chronicles 11:7",
      "text": "Beth-zur, Soco, Adullam,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:second-chronicles.11.8",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "second-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Chronicles 11:8",
      "text": "Gath, Mareshah, Ziph,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:second-chronicles.11.9",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "second-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Chronicles 11:9",
      "text": "Adoraim, Lachish, Azekah,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:second-chronicles.11.10",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "second-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Chronicles 11:10",
      "text": "Zorah, Aijalon, and Hebron, fortified cities which are in Judah and in Benjamin.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:second-chronicles.11.11",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "second-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Chronicles 11:11",
      "text": "He made the fortresses strong, and put commanders in them, and stores of food, oil, and wine.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:second-chronicles.11.12",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "second-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Chronicles 11:12",
      "text": "And he put shields and spears in all the cities, and made them very strong. So he held Judah and Benjamin.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:second-chronicles.11.13",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "second-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Chronicles 11:13",
      "text": "And the priests and the Levites that were in all Israel resorted to him from all places where they lived.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:second-chronicles.11.14",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "second-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Chronicles 11:14",
      "text": "For the Levites left their common lands and their holdings and came to Judah and Jerusalem, because Jeroboam and his sons cast them out from serving as priests of the Lord,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:second-chronicles.11.15",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "second-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Chronicles 11:15",
      "text": "and he appointed his own priests for the high places, and for the satyrs, and for the calves which he had made.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:second-chronicles.11.16",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "second-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Chronicles 11:16",
      "text": "And those who had set their hearts to seek the Lord God of Israel came after them from all the tribes of Israel to Jerusalem to sacrifice to the Lord, the God of their fathers.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:second-chronicles.11.17",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "second-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Chronicles 11:17",
      "text": "They strengthened the kingdom of Judah, and for three years they made Rehoboam the son of Solomon secure, for they walked for three years in the way of David and Solomon.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:second-chronicles.11.18",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "second-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Chronicles 11:18",
      "text": "Rehoboam took as wife Mahalath the daughter of Jerimoth the son of David, and of Abihail the daughter of Eliab the son of Jesse;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:second-chronicles.11.19",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "second-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Chronicles 11:19",
      "text": "and she bore him sons, Jeush, Shemariah, and Zaham.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:second-chronicles.11.20",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "second-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Chronicles 11:20",
      "text": "After her he took Maacah the daughter of Absalom, who bore him Abijah, Attai, Ziza, and Shelomith.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:second-chronicles.11.21",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "second-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Chronicles 11:21",
      "text": "Rehoboam loved Maacah the daughter of Absalom above all his wives and concubines (he took eighteen wives and sixty concubines, and had twenty-eight sons and sixty daughters);",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:second-chronicles.11.22",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "second-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Chronicles 11:22",
      "text": "and Rehoboam appointed Abijah the son of Maacah as chief prince among his brothers, for he intended to make him king.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:second-chronicles.11.23",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "second-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Chronicles 11:23",
      "text": "And he dealt wisely, and distributed some of his sons through all the districts of Judah and Benjamin, in all the fortified cities; and he gave them abundant provisions, and procured wives for them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
